    {
        "client_msg_id": "9e1a2ff4-f4a4-4cbc-949d-3e6a2bb970d4",
        "type": "message",
        "text": "Ask them to write a section of a blog\/pitch article ideas\/do a campaign strategy\/write an outline, not a whole blog post. You'll get more applicants. I recommend a test that could reasonably be done during someone's lunch break, so, 45-60 mins. This is super important for DEI and making sure the playing field is level for people who may be working 2 jobs, be primary child caretakers, etc. It should not devour their week. I was paid $75 in an Amazon gift card (probably a tax workaround) for a 90 minute timed test. I think the minimum to be respectful should be $75. If you can pay more, you'll wow applicants and tell them a lot about how much you'll respect their work when they're hired. Hope that helps!",
        "user": "U01FUP6AMEZ",
